Twenty years ago, MSF was the first organisation to bring ARVs to a public health facility in Kenya.Globally, millions of people lost their lives before the battle was over, but in the end HIV drugs eventually became available because of the defeat of the pharmaceutical monopolies. The news the world was anticipating finally broke: A vaccine against Covid-19 is now a reality. Unfortunately, the news that made the western world cheer and stock markets skyrocket, did not give people in poorer countries the same reason to jump for joy.
Rich countries have, on one hand, grabbed most of the available vaccines for themselves by pre-ordering some 80 per cent of the doses and, on the other hand, blocked a measure that could enable other parts of the world to provide for themselves: A patent waiver on all Covid-related products and vaccines for as long as the pandemic is ongoing.



