Instead, the WTO and wealthy countries across the world contribute to maintaining the victim role of low-income countries with their refusal to support this waiver.
The patent waver proposal will be discussed again at the WTO TRIPS Council on Thursday 10 December. MSF asks governments across the world to practice the solidarity they preach.
Now is the time to raise our voices in support for a proposal that represents a real chance for people whose lives are threatened by a pandemic we face a long struggle to defeat.
